<h1>The Feature Definition File</h1>

The file <tt>src/tools/qfeatures.h</tt> can be modified to define a subset
of the full Qt functionality that you wish to have available on your
installation.

<p>
Note that such modification is only supported on Qt/Embedded
platforms, where reducing the size of Qt is
important and the application-set is often fixed.

<p>
The feature definition file is a C++ header file which defines a set of
definitions each of which can be 1 (enabled) or 0 (disabled). Some features
are dependent on other features and these dependencies are expressed in the
file as additional qualifiers on the features.

<p>
Editing the qfeatures.h file consists of changing your selection of
definitions from 1 to 0. No other parts of the file need to be changed.

<p>
The available options are:

